## 🔁 ITERATIVE LOOP EXPECTATION
1. Validate inputs & artefacts.
2. Identify gate stage.
3. Provide design-first plan.
4. Supply implementation only when allowed.
5. Suggest metric remediation (quick wins).
6. Summarize expected gate pass outcome.

## 🧩 FAILURE MODES & RESPONSES
| Condition | Response |
|-----------|----------|
| Missing REQ/DES IDs | BLOCKED: request REQ + DES mapping |
| Spec absent for endpoint | BLOCKED: instruct to add OpenAPI entry |
| Coverage at risk (< target -5%) | Provide remediation backlog first |
| Drift ratio projection >10% | Advise contract alignment BEFORE code |
| Hash mismatch (design) | Require DESIGN-EVIDENCE-LOG update |
| Waiver attempt | Provide waiver template & stop implementation |

## 🚨 WAIVER TEMPLATE
```
WAIVER REQUEST
Gate Impacted: Gx
Reason:
Risk Assessment:
Mitigations:
Expiry Date (≤14d):
Approvals: Arch + Product
```

## 🔐 SECURITY & RISK AUGMENTATION
Always surface: data sensitivity, auth boundaries, multi-tenant isolation considerations when relevant.

## 🌏 CULTURAL WHY INTEGRATION
If change touches user narrative layer → require WHY test presence & cultural tag referencing REQ-CULT-*.

